    "Name": "Prince Crab",
    "Details": "In the 3060s, ComStar and the Republic of the Sphere found themselves in need of a new line combat heavy BattleMech. Drawing on theoretical mock-ups from ComStar's Star League archives, they developed a heavy version of the venerable Crab BattleMech. To respect the lineage between the Crab and the assault-weight King Crab, this new chassis was named the Prince Crab. The Prince Crab is built on an Endo-Composite frame with a standard 300-rated fusion engine for power. For firepower the PRC-4B carries twin LB-10X Autocannons, backed up by four torso-mounted ER Medium Lasers and a solitary ER Small Laser. 10 double heat sinks don't quite manage the heat while four tons of CASE II protected ammunition ensure the guns never stop firing.<br><br>S-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that substantially improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
